      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your eye symptoms sound like they could be a sign of conjunctivitis, but it's also possible that prolonged screen time is causing irritation. If it's just dryness, lubricating eye drops can help, but if it's an infection, you might need an antibiotic. I recommend using a preservative-free formula to avoid further irritation. If the redness and discharge persist, consider a warm compress and avoid touching your eye. If it's still bothering you after a couple of days, you should see a doctor. Remember, I'm not a doctor, so always consult a professional for a proper diagnosis.",
